# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
# .env.local is gitignored and loaded automatically by electron-vite during dev.
#
# DEPRECATED — see services/fs-sync/config.example.json
#
# FT5_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID and FT5_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET were used
# to inline the Google Drive OAuth client into the desktop main-process
# bundle at build time via electron-vite's `define` map. They are no
# longer consumed by the build (the `define` entries were dropped in
# `implement-datasource-onboarding`).
#
# OAuth app config now lives at the service-owned file:
#   ~/ft5/sync_app/config.json   (Linux / macOS)
#   %USERPROFILE%\ft5\sync_app\config.json   (Windows)
#
# Copy services/fs-sync/config.example.json to that path and edit
# clientId / clientSecret for each provider you intend to use. See the
# README "Provider OAuth registration (one-time setup)" section.
#
# The two vars below are kept commented-out as a migration breadcrumb
# for contributors on the old `.env.local` workflow. Setting them has
# no effect on the running app.
#
# FT5_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
# FT5_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
